ECADUPSPCBReferenceDesignatorInfo: defines the Reference Designator to be used for the Printed Circuit Board in the Product Structure
ECADUPSPackageNamePropertyInfo: defines the name of the ECAD property of the Altium Component which is used to derived the Package name during initial import
ECADUPSPackageDescriptionPropertyInfo: defines the name of the ECAD property of the Altium Component which is used to derived the Package Description during initial import
ECADUPSUseClassificationInfo: defines if Library Classification or local categories should be used for electronic Components
ECADUPSElectronicLibraryInfo:
defines the Classification Library and Classes used for classifying the Electronic Components. Only Definition Libraries are supported, no Categorization Libraries.
You can use either the name of the classification library or class or the title and multiple Libraries can be separated by a semicolon.
Example:Library-1;Library-2/class-1/class-2
AltiumUPSECADCategoriesInfo: Component Categories used if Library Classification is not selected
AltiumUPSEnterpriseItemNumberPropertyInf: Defines the name of the Altium Parameter which holds the Enterprise Item Number
ECADClassificationPathDefinitionProperty: Defines the name of the Altium Parameter to store the classification path for import
AltiumUPSCheckoutFolderNamingInfo: Defines the naming Convention for the directory into which the data is opened. Can be Name, Title or Name_Title
